Bambusa tulda

   [3627.jpg]
    Authority   Roxb.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3627

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A thick-walled evergreen or deciduous bamboo reachnig a height of 20-24
   m under favourable conditions.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial evergreen or deciduous bamboo.
   COMMON NAMES
   Tulda, Mita, Mitinga, Makla, Peka, Mitenga, Jowa, Kiranti, Wamuna,
   Bijuli, Thaikwa.
   FURTHER INF
   Tulda is native of Bangladesh and Myanmar. In Myanmar, it is common on
   flat alluvial land along streams in the mixed deciduous forests and
   along the banks of dry water-couses. Bamboos grow between the latitudes
   40°N and S. Though the big bamboo forests usually occur between 15-25°N
   and S.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Hassan M 1988 pp 505-513 [RAIN, TEMP, SAL, DRA, TEXT, PH, DEP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 417 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 8 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Banik R 1988 pp 576
   Troup R 1921 pp 978 1001 [TEXT, DRA, USE]

